The paper deals with the construction of measurement matrices in compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Computational Geometry (cs.CG). However, since the paper focuses on the construction of measurement matrices, which is a fundamental problem in compressed sensing, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) is also a likely sub-category since the paper deals with the optimization of the mutual incoherence of the measurement matrix. Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) are less likely sub-categories since they are not directly related to the problem of constructing measurement matrices.
